<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 9800 MODEL - TESTING THE RIGHT FRONT MODULATOR,
        PART B
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING THE RIGHT FRONT MODULATOR, PART B</title>
        <table id="t0403509" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing the Right Front Modulator, Part B</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="s1t7" align="center"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>TEST POINTS</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Disconnect controller connector (627) and right front modulator connector (360). At
                                connector (627) measure resistance between terminals C1, E1, D1 and all other terminals
                                in the connector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(627) (360) C1 to E1 C1 to D1 D1 to E1</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate short circuit between any terminals where resistance is less than 100K ohms,
                                then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (627) use test lead to jumper terminal C1 to ground. At connector (360)
                                measure resistance to ground at terminal B.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(627), C1 to gnd. (360), B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open in wire between connectors (627) and (360), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (627) use test lead to jumper terminal C1 to E1. At connector (360)
                                measure resistance between B and A.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(627) C1 to E1 (360) B to A.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open in wire between connectors (627) and (360), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At connector (627) use test lead to jumper terminal C1 to D1. At connector (360)
                                measure resistance between terminals B and C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>(627) C1 to D1 (360) B to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Locate open in wire between connectors (627) and (360), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At the M-21/M22 modulator valve body connector, measure resistance between Hold and
                                Source terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Hold to Source terminal.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>3.5 to 5.0 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace the M-21/ M-22 modulator valve.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At the M-21/M-22 modulator valve body connector, measure resistance between Exhaust
                                and Source terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Exhaust to Source terminal.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>3.5 to 5.0 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace the M-21/M-22 modulator valve.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At the M-21/M-22 modulator valve body connector, measure resistance between Exhaust
                                and Hold terminals.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Exhaust to Hold terminal.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>7 to 10 Ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next Step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace the M-21/ M-22 modulator valve.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>At the M-21/M-22 modulator connector, measure resistance between all three terminals
                                and ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Hold to gnd, Source to gnd, Exhaust to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Replace the M-21/ M-22 modulator valve.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Connect (360) to modulator valve and (627) to controller. Turn Key ON and pass magnet
                                over reset. Note condition of LEDs. Are Red LEDs ON?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Red LEDs ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Repeat
                                <hotlnk document="s04035v_7.xml" xrefid="t0403501">INITIAL START-UP TEST PROCEDURE
                                    <xref refid="t0403501"/>.
                                </hotlnk>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Note if the same LEDs are illuminated as before the test.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>Replace the controller.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04035v_10.xml" xrefid="t0403504">INSPECTION FOR ILLUMINATED LEDS,
                                    PART B
                                    <xref refid="t0403504"/>.
                                </hotlnk>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
